Celebrate World Down Syndrome Day with dance!

Recently, artists of @uniteddance.official had the unique chance to express themselves in the MFA's galleries. A beautiful reminder that when given the opportunity, creative potential is unlimited, no matter who you are. Happy #WorldDownSyndromeDay!

@uniteddance.official offers made-to-measure dance courses in Europe and the USA for youth and young adults with Down syndrome.

@shelterinplacegallery is both a historical marker of the COVID-19 lockdown and an innovative artistic response to a moment of crisis.

Throughout the lockdown and beyond, @ebenhaines has used his scale model of a contemporary art gallery—where one inch equals one foot—to showcase miniature works by fellow artists. He and his gallery partner Delany Dameron have used Instagram to stage multiple exhibitions, drawing interest from around the world.

Inside "New Light: Encounters and Connections," the original model of the gallery features works both old and new: miniature vases by 20th-century French art potter Auguste Delaherche and a tiny wood vessel, made from individual segments of cedar wood, by @alisoncroney. Eben and Alison recently stopped by the exhibition to view their works together ✨
